oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of two American soldiers
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pettis Graham Gordon served as a bugler and courier. He was from Christiana, Rutherford County, Tennessee. Knox Newman was from Fayetteville, Lincoln County, Tennessee. Both men served in 323rd Inf. Regt., 81st Div.
